## Use Case - UC-012 : Inventory management system

    This is an inventory management system for a retail or warehouse business. This system tracks stock levels, manages suppliers, handles purchase orders, triggers reorder alerts, and maintains a complete audit trail of all stock movements

# Use case details

Actors :- Store manager, Warehouse Staff, Supplier, System(Reorder Scheduler)

Preconditions :- Product catalog is setup with SKU codes. Suppliers are registered. Minimum  stock thresholds are configured per product

Trigger :- A new stock shipment arrives, or stock falls below the reorder threshold.

Main Flow :-    1. Staff receives shipment and scans product SKUs
                2. System updates stock quantity for each product.
                3. System records goods-received note(GRN) with quantity, date, and supplier.
                4. Manager monitors stock levels via dashboard.
                5. When stock falls below reorder level, system auto generates a purchase order(PO)
                6. Manager approves PO and sends to supplier.
                7. Supplier fulfils order; stock updated on receipt.
                8. System logs every stock movement in the audit trail
        
Alternate Flow  :-   
                    A1: Received quantoty differs from PO quantity -> Flag discrepancy; allow partial accepatance
                    A2: Product not in catalog -> Prompt staff to register new product.
                    A3: Supplier delivers expired goods -> Mark as rejected; raise return order.
                    A4: Manager manually adjusts stocks(damage,theft) -> Require reason code; log adjustment.

Exception Flow :- 
                    E1: SKU not found -> 'Product SKU not recognized' error.
                    E2: Negative stock after adjustment -> Block and alert manager.
                    E3: Duplicate GRN for same PO -> 'GRN already recorded for this PO' error.
                    E4: PO approved but supplier not responding -> Escalation alert after 48 hours.
                    E5: Unauthorized stock adjustment -> 'Insufficient privileges' error.

Postconditions :- Stock levels updataed. GRNrecorde. PO status updated. Audit trail entry added. Reorder alert cleared if stock now above the threshold.

Non-functional :- Stock dashboard refreshes in real time. Audit trail must be immutable. Reorder alert triggered within 1 minute of threshold breach. System supports 50,000 SKUs and 500 concurrent users

# Class Design

1.  Class - Product
    Attributes - sku, name, category, unit, reorderLevel, currentStock, supplierId
    Key methods - updateStock(), isLowStock(), getStockHistory()

2.  Class - Supplier
    Attributes - supplierId, name, contact, email, leadTimeDays, products[]
    Key methods - createPO(), getDeliveryHistory()

3.  Class - PurchaseOrder
    Attributes - poId, supplierId, items[], status, createdDate, approvedDate
    Key methods - approve(), send(), receive(), cancel()

4.  Class - GoodsReceived
    Attributes - grnId, poId, receivedItems[], receivedDate, staffId, discrepancies[]
    Key methods - record(), flagDiscrepancy(), close()

5.  Class - StockMovement
    Attributes - movementId, sku, type, quantity, reason, staffId, timestamp
    Key methods - log(), getAuditTrail()

6.  Class - Warehouse
    Attributes - warehouseId, name, location, products[], zones[]
    Key methods - getDashboard(), triggerReorder(), getAlerts()

# Stock Movement Types

1.  Movement Type - RECEIPT
    Trigger - Goods received from supplier
    Stock Effect - (+quantity)
    Requires Approval - No

2.  Movement Type - SALE
    Trigger - Product sold to customer
    Stock Effect - (-quantity)
    Requires Approval - No

3.  Movement Type - ADJUSTMENT
    Trigger - MAnual correction (damage/theft)
    Stock Effect - (+/-quantity)
    Requires Approval - Yes

4.  Movement Type - RETURN
    Trigger - Customer returns product
    Stock Effect - (+quantity)
    Requires Approval - No

5.  Movement Type - WRITE_OFF
    Trigger - Expired or unsellable goods
    Stock Effect - (-quantity)
    Requires Approval - Yes

6.  Movement Type - TRANSFER
    Trigger - Between warehouses/zones
    Stock Effect - (+/-quantity)
    Requires Approval - No


# How to run this project
1. Open PowerShell in this folder.
2. Run tests: python -m unittest discover -s tests
3. Run demo: python run_demo.py
4. User case inputs: python inventory_app.py

